\par }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs20 {This value is the fastest sample rate currently displayed in the Sent and Received graphs.  Note that the Max values can exceed the rated speed of your modem.   Please see the }{\i 
Modem Connections}{ section at the bottom of this page for more information.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s3\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \shading2500 \b\f1\fs20\cf2 {Auto Scale
\par }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs20 {Each of the graphs provide an Auto Scale option whi
ch dynamically adjusts the range of the graph so that all bars, or lines, are drawn completely within the graph.  Auto Scale is recommended if you are using a high bandwidth device such as cable, DSL, or T1 line.
\par 
\par Modem users may wish to manually configure
 the range of the graph to match the rated speed of their modem.  For example, if you have a 56 kbps modem, set the graph display mode to bps, and adjust the slider control so that the topmost value in the graph displays 56k bits/sec.   
\par 
\par The slider control for the Scale is disabled if the Auto Scale option is selected, however, the slider will automatically move according to the average data rate.
\par 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\sa120\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\outlinelevel1\adjustright \shading2500 \b\i\f1\cf12 {Display Panel
